---
comment: |-
  deno is a modern JavaScript/TypeScript runtime. It can be abused to run arbitrary scripts, fetch remote code, and escalate privileges via permission flags.
functions:
  file-read:
  - code: |-
      deno run --allow-read=/etc/shadow read.js
    contexts:
      unprivileged:
        comment: |-
          Reads sensitive files if permission flags are enabled.
  file-write:
  - code: |-
      deno run --allow-write=/tmp/write.js
    contexts:
      unprivileged:
        comment: |-
          Writes arbitrary content to files when allowed.
  inherit:
  - code: |-
      deno run --allow-run=less pager.js
    comment: |-
      The `--allow-run` flag permits spawning external programs. This can be abused to inherit execution from system binaries like `less`.
    contexts:
      unprivileged:
    from: less
...
